      <guid>http://oncodesign.io/2012/08/18/attaching-a-file-in-cordova--uploading-it-with-jquery-mobile/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;This post is for those unlucky souls who are tasked with developing an Android solution that attaches a file to an HTML form using Cordova and uploads the form via jQuery Mobile. Documentation on these topics is scarce so I&amp;rsquo;ve created a &lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/claudemamo/file-attach-cordova-upload-jqm&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34;&gt;minimal example&lt;/a&gt; on my GitHub page demonstrating how to do this. Instructions to run the example are found inside the project&amp;rsquo;s README file.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;separator&#34; style=&#34;clear: both; text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-kp8H1mifMbs/UC9nIB8Fz6I/AAAAAAAAACs/0PXgtGZ8cEs/s1600/attaching-file.png&#34; imageanchor=&#34;1&#34; style=&#34;margin-left: 1em; margin-right: 1em;&#34;&gt;&lt;img border=&#34;0&#34; height=&#34;640&#34; src=&#34;http://4.bp.blogspot.com/-kp8H1mifMbs/UC9nIB8Fz6I/AAAAAAAAACs/0PXgtGZ8cEs/s640/attaching-file.png&#34; width=&#34;384&#34; /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;separator&#34; style=&#34;clear: both; text-align: center;&#34;&gt;&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
